Task 2: Test Consumer Rebalancing
Step 1: Produce Test Messages
In a new terminal, produce messages to the topic:

cd $KAFKA_HOME

# Produce 20 test messages
for i in {1..20}; do
  echo "order-$i:Product purchased - Order ID: $i, Amount: \$$(($i * 10))" | \
  $KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-console-producer.sh \
    --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
    --topic orders \
    --property "parse.key=true" \
    --property "key.separator=:"
done
Observe which consumers receive which messages based on partition assignment.

Step 2: Trigger Rebalancing by Adding a Consumer
Open a third terminal and start another consumer:

cd ~/kafka-lab/consumers
python3 consumer_group_member.py consumer-3
Observe:

Existing consumers will pause briefly
Partitions will be redistributed
All consumers will resume with new partition assignments
Check the new partition distribution:

$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --group order-processing-group \
  --describe
Step 3: Trigger Rebalancing by Removing a Consumer
Stop one consumer (press Ctrl+C in Terminal 1).

Observe:

Remaining consumers detect the member leaving
Partitions are redistributed among remaining consumers
Processing continues without message loss
Verify the rebalance:

$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh \
  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
  --group order-processing-group \
  --describe
Step 4: Test Consumer Group Lag
Create a script to monitor lag:

cat > monitor_lag.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "Monitoring Consumer Group Lag..."
echo "Press Ctrl+C to stop"
echo ""

while true; do
  clear
  date
  echo "================================"
  $KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-consumer-groups.sh \
    --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
    --group order-processing-group \
    --describe
  sleep 5
done
EOF

chmod +x monitor_lag.sh
Run the monitoring script in a separate terminal:

cd ~/kafka-lab/consumers
./monitor_lag.sh
Stop all consumers and produce more messages to observe lag increase:

# Produce 50 more messages
for i in {21..70}; do
  echo "order-$i:Product purchased - Order ID: $i, Amount: \$$(($i * 10))" | \
  $KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-console-producer.sh \
    --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
    --topic orders \
    --property "parse.key=true" \
    --property "key.separator=:"
done
