Test rebalancing worked:
Start 2 consumers: Each should get 2 partitions
Add 3rd consumer: Partitions redistribute (2-1-1 or similar)
Remove 1 consumer: Remaining consumers pick up orphaned partitions
Verify Message Processing
Check total messages consumed:
# Count messages in topic
$KAFKA_HOME/bin/kafka-run-class.sh kafka.tools.GetOffsetShell \
  --broker-list localhost:9092 \
  --topic orders
Verify no message loss:
Total messages produced should equal sum of all partition offsets
Each message should be consumed exactly once per consumer group
Troubleshooting Tips
Consumer not joining group:

Verify Kafka broker is running: jps | grep Kafka
Check network connectivity: netstat -an | grep 9092
Review consumer logs for connection errors
Rebalancing takes too long:

Reduce session.timeout.ms in consumer configuration
Ensure heartbeat.interval.ms < session.timeout.ms / 3
Messages not distributing evenly:

Verify topic has multiple partitions
Check if using key-based partitioning (messages with same key go to same partition)
Consumer lag increasing:

Scale up consumer instances
Optimize message processing logic
Increase consumer fetch size
